<p>
<h2>How to mirror NomadBSD</h2>

<h3>What to mirror</h3>
<p>
<a href="https://nomadbsd.org/download">https://nomadbsd.org/download</a>
</p>

<h3>Expected mirror size</h3>
<p>
The mirror won't require more than 50GB.
</p>

<h3>Mirror update frequency</h3>
<p>
Once a day
</p>

<h3>How to mirror</h3>
<p>
Via <a href="https://lftp.tech/">lftp</a>:
<pre class="code">
lftp -e 'mirror --delete https://nomadbsd.org/download /target/directory'
</pre>
Or via <a href="https://www.gnu.org/software/wget/">wget</a>:
<pre class="code">
wget --no-host-directories --mirror --no-directories -P /target/directory https://nomadbsd.org/download
</pre>
</p>

<h3>Announce a new mirror</h3>
<p>
If you have created a mirror for NomadBSD let us know via mirror [at] nomadbsd [dot] org
</p>
CONTENT_END
</p>

